to avoid resource waste, we label nodes 'Large', 'Small' etc. making sure that the proper size of pod will be scheduled into the right node.
set node size in pod definition file:
spec.nodeSelector.size

then:
$ k create -f pod-definition.yaml

to set the size of a node, run
$ k label nodes <node-name> <label-key>=<label-value>
eg. k label nodes node01 size=Large

but if we need to set Large or Medium, or Not Small these complicated values, we need to use node affinity
